ved unable to cut wasteful spending as much as it promised, and does not have high hopes for the new Cabinet. While promoting the TPP and fiscal reconstruction are the right steps, the DPJ is divided over these policies as many in the party claim there was no mention of a sales tax hike in the campaign platform and fear the TPP risks devastating the agriculture industry, Saito said.


